A. Project Overview
Problem Statement: Financial institutions need real-time fraud detection that adapts to evolving fraud patterns while maintaining low false positive rates and high throughput.

Real-World Use Case: A payment processor needs to screen 10,000+ transactions per second, flagging suspicious activity with <1% false positives and <50ms latency.

Target Users: Payment processors, banks, e-commerce platforms, fintech developers.

B. Tech Stack
Language: Python 3.9+

ML Framework: Scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM

Deep Learning: PyTorch (for neural network models)

Feature Store: Feast

Model Serving: FastAPI, Ray Serve

Monitoring: MLflow, Evidently AI

Data Processing: Apache Spark (PySpark), Pandas

Database: PostgreSQL (for metadata), Redis (for caching)

Tools: Docker, Airflow, DVC, Git LFS
